AR500 Armor® 6” x 8” Side Plate Level III Body Armor – Patent Pending

AR500 Armor® Level III Body Armor is manufactured from an extremely rugged ballistic grade steel core and coated with our PAXCON (a division of Line-X) spall and fragmentation protective coating. Our ballistic steel plate is unmatched in the industry and is formulated and treated specifically to our specifications for improved consistency, durability, and then tested to NIJ standards. Our ballistic plate core is stress fracture resistant, features an ultra-low profile ballistic core of only 0.26”, and is designed to handle extreme abuse in day to day use, training, and less than ideal storage conditions. AR500 Armor® body armor will outlast alternative armor solutions such as Ceramic, Dyneema, UHMWPE, and raw/uncoated steel trauma plates.

Level III Rating: AR500 Armor® body armor is Stand-Alone and Multi-hit capable. Designed to defeat rifle threats up to 7.62x51 M80 NATO Ball (.308 Winchester) at velocities up to 2,780 feet per second and all pistol calibers.

AR500 Armor® 6” x 8” side armor plates provide light weight and ultra slim rifle threat protection to the sides of your plate carrier. The enormous benefit of their thin 0.26” ballistic core shines when you’re physically wearing the side plates, particularly on an inside the cummerbund side plate pouch. Our 6” x 8” side plates are thinner than Ceramic and other comparable side plates, and are on par with the profile of soft inserts but with increased rifle threat protection. Improve ergonomics and comfort by having less interference from your side plates with our AR500 Armor® 6” x 8” side plates. These will fit in standard plate pockets that are capable of accepting 6” x 6”, 6” x 8”, and 8” x 8” side armor plates. The orientation on the 6” x 8” side plate armor is intended to be worn with the 8” side vertical.

title: For Sale:  Desert Eagle In 44 and 357 - 2 Guns In One!
postcontent:
Own An Icon and A Powerhouse Pistol

The Desert Eagle has been immortalized in movies and video games, probably because of its instantly recognizable shape and massive, rapid-fire power. Whatever the reason, the Desert Eagle has a reputation as a seriously respected handgun.

The Desert Eagle is a True "Hand Cannon"

In a class by itself, the Desert Eagle uses a gas-operated mechanism normally found in rifles. Lesser semi-automatic pistols use a short recoil or blow-back design.

With a rotating artillery-style bolt like the M-16 and a reliable, recoil-absorbing gas system like the Mini-14, the Desert Eagle is strong enough to handle the stoutest loads you’ll want to feed it.

For All Its Massive Power, The Desert Eagle Handles Like a Pussycat

It’s a BIG pussycat for sure, but the recoil is surprisingly manageable and controllable. The massive rotating bolt with its reliable gas operation smooths out recoil, and the large and ideally sculpted grip and generous top tang helps direct recoil forces straight back instead of whipping upward and to the left like most magnum revolvers do. This makes muzzle rise minimal and follow-up shots quick, easy, and accurate.

Two Guns in One – A Rare Find

This Desert Eagle has an uncommon bonus. The .44 is the highly desirable early Israeli made IMI model WITH an extra scoped .357 barrel assembly. The extra scoped .357 top end allows quick, easy caliber interchangeability. In other words, it is essentially "two guns in one."

The pistol is a .44 Remington magnum early (small safety lever) Mark VII in bright nickel finish. It has been fitted with a MK VII adjustable trigger and IMI Desert Eagle Rubber grips made by Hogue. It is powerful, accurate, reliable, and fun to shoot.

The .357 top end (barrel, slide, bolt, recoil springs and guides) is an Israeli-made Mark VII type in black, fitted with a Bushnell Phantom 1.3x scope on custom mounts. It has been shot little and is wickedly accurate.

This package includes:
·         IMI Desert Eagle MK VII Bright Nickel finish in .44 magnum with IMI adjustable trigger and IMI (Hogue) rubber grips
·         1 Nickel .44 magnum 8 round magazine
·         3 Black .44 magnum 8 round magazines
·         IMI Desert Eagle MK VII Black .357 top end assembly
·         4 black .357 9 round magazines
·         Original IMI MK I non-adjustable trigger group
·         Original IMI Desert Eagle one-piece hard grips
·         Bushnell Phantom 1.3x scope on custom mounts. (Mounted to the .357 top end)
·         IMI Desert Eagle marked Cordura belt holster
·         Cordura / nylon tactical thigh rig holster
·         IMI cleaning / maintenance tool

Everything is in excellent condition – no scratches or scars. It was my steel plate gun and was only ever used at range competitions.

As you know, this is a gas-operated, rotating bolt pistol – it has the strength of a rifle action. While it will handle the stoutest loads that you can find, I have always loaded it moderately, for accuracy. Neither the .44 or the .357 barrels have ever seen a non-jacketed or cast bullet – the gas systems are clean! The polygon rifling increases velocity and accuracy and is easy to keep clean.

You get 2 guns in one --- a .44 and a .357 ---,8 mags, scope and mount, spare trigger and grips, tool, and 2 holsters – WOW! The entire package is only $2300.

Go ahead and price out the individual components – you’ll see that this is a very good deal!

I will consider trade offers for a 1995 or newer full-size extended cab pickup truck in very good condition – but no “monster truck” or race truck mods please.

"The .357 Combat Magnum Stainless"

Shipped from the Smith & Wesson Factory in 1973 is this Very Special model 66 (No Dash) .357 Magnum Revolver. Whats special about it is the fact that it retains it's original Stainless Sights signifying that it is an early production Model 66. Many were customized after purchase by Police Officers and Security Officers alike.
